$interpreted: Kind Farmer: General Feiz, keeping innocent civilians captive is against the law.
Angry Farmer: Release them right away! They are no longer bandits anymore!
Feiz: You mindless rioters...I order you to disband, now!
Kind Farmer: These bandits have changed for good already. Please ask Queen Angelia to pardon them!
Angry Farmer: They only robbed the food caravan out of desperation, since there was simply no food during the war. They didn't hurt anybody at all!
Feiz: Silence! Looks like I'm going to have to apprehend all of you!
Feiz: The person who can cast this type of high-level arcane magic...
Fredrica: Ara~ Isn't this serious little Feizy? It has been a long time~
Feiz: —— Lucien!!
Feiz: I told you many times before. Do NOT call me by that nickname!
Fredrica: What's wrong with the nickname? Little Feizy is a cute name~ You can call me little Fred too. That makes us even~
Feiz: I! RE! FUSE!
Fredrica: Good thing that handsome decided to come and notify me.
Fredrica: Little Feizy, you went overboard this time. Why did you assault the civilians?

Feiz: Queen Angelia stationed me here.
Suppressing the civilians is part of my duty, to begin with!
Jerome: That's incorrect. Our duty should be to protect the civilians!
Fredrica: Looks like we can't talk sense into you anymore. Gotta do this the hard way then.
Feiz: Damnit, what a shameful display...how did I lose to a woman like her who has no principles...
Jerome: From the very moment you abandoned the people, you'd already lost to General Lucien.
Feiz: Nonsense! Quit using those fancy words! All she did was abandon her former king in order to please the new queen.
Feiz: A shameless traitor like her who serves any random king doesn't deserve to be a soldier! Much less a general! How amusing!
Feiz: I'm absolutely going to report your violations to the queen!
Fredrica: Yeah yeah, go ahead. Little Feizy, you really haven't changed one bit~
Fredrica: Escort general Feiz back to the capitol. The queen should be informed about the situation already.
Jerome: ......
Jerome: General Lucien, please forgive me for my previous impudence. I used to have the same misunderstanding general Feiz has.
Fredrica: Ara~ So you don't hate me now?
Jerome: General, you chose to stay in Kingdom of the Sun and remained a member of the military because that is what allows you to protect the civilians.
Fredrica: ......
Jerome: You do not care about who becomes king or queen.
Jerome: Because the one you pledged loyalty to is not the king of this country, but its people.
Jerome: ...That's my speculation. Am I right?
Fredrica: Handsome, you do realize that a woman with mystique is the most charming, right? I will neither admit nor deny your speculation~
Jerome: Certainly. I've been around you for quite a long time. I'm already used to that part of you, at the very least.
Jerome: ...General, would you be willing to allow me back to your ranks?
Fredrica: Well, usually I'm not the type who backslides in a relationship...however, since handsome is so good looking, I can't help but forgive you~
Jerome: Does this mean that you agree?
Fredrica: However~ I have just ONE condition~~
Forgetful Tom: Congrats on returning to the army!
Late Peter: It's all thanks to officer Muca for speaking up for me, as well as General Lucien for accepting my explanation.
Forgetful Tom: Speaking of which, turns out that the queen assigned two generals to rule over Jersey,
Late Peter: not because she wanted to keep general Lucien under surveillance, but because she was worried about general Feiz's extreme actions.
Jerome: General....I'm not taking it off......
Fredrica: Stop whining. If you call yourself a man, then get naked~ If you don't want to take it off yourself, I'm going to barge in and give you a hand~
Jerome: Alright, alright... I'll take it off myself... Please don't come in here, I beg you...
Late Peter: I have to go rescue officer Muca!
Forgetful Tom: Dude, can't you read the atmosphere? Let's go.
Jerome: General, do I have to wear something like this...?
Fredrica: You're the one who said that you would do one thing for me~A good man doesn't go back on his words~~
Jerome: Is it really okay to wear something like this on the battlefield?
Fredrica: No need to worry. A handsome man is always handsome no matter what he wears~
Jerome: That's not my concern. Isn't this cape a bit...too extravagant?
Fredrica: Not at all, not at all~We look like a couple with matching outfits, don't you think~?
Jerome: ...General, I see that your habit of teasing others has not diminished one bit.
Fredrica: I'm actually not that interested in teasing other people.
Fredrica: I only like to tease you, handsome, and ONLY you~
Jerome: General Lucien!
Fredrica: Looking forward to working with you again, officer Jerome.
Jerome: I'm starting to regret transferring back here...
Fredrica: Well~ it's already too~ late to regret now~ ❤
